The paper deals with algorithms for answering geometric queries, which is a central topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of algebraic computation trees and arithmetic-geometric tools suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of data structures (cs.DS) and scientific computing (cs.SC). The paper also discusses the construction of a database, which is a topic in database management (cs.DM). Finally, the paper mentions the use of example classes of systems of polynomial equations, which may be relevant to the sub-category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
